headline.main: RABAUL RAID SETS THREE SHIPS AFIRE; Allied Bombers Leave 24,000 Japanese Tonnage in Flames After Heavy Attack

lead_paragraph: AT UNITED NATIONS HEADQUARTERS, Australia, Saturday, Jan. 2 (U.P.) -- Allied forces in the Buna sector of New Guinea have driven a second wedge through to the sea, splitting defending Japanese forces into three groups, and our bombers in a New Year's Day raid on Rabaul struck three Japanese merchantmen totaling 24,000 tons with 1,000-pound bombs, General MacArthur's noon communique said today.
abstract: Allied bombers fire 3 Jap ships, Rabaul
